the previous prototype was an attempt to make a VM inspired by Nock. some problems:
- lists turned out to be quite a bit less useful than expected given that many of Nock's design decisions were based on pairs
- i couldn't manage to construct decrement properly
- i had to faff around with the design quite a bit though it was fun i guess (ofc lots of design time is to be expected, this is Heliodex/VM after all)
however i learned a ton so whatever

let's make another prototype. it will look a little like a programming language at first though. i want to take less significant inspiration in order to see if i can make the simplest thing my mind will jump to


TYPES

it's gonna be the classic 3: Lists (ordered sets of Things), Nums (non-negative integers), Things (Lists or Nums)


OPERATIONS

[.x] -> x

*[x y .z] -> *[*[x y] .z]

*[x F] -> x

*[[.x] INC] -> [x INC]
*[x INC] -> x + 1

*[[[.x] y] ADD] -> *[[x y] ADD]
*[[x [.y]] ADD] -> *[[x y] ADD]
*[[x y] ADD] -> x + y
*[x ADD] -> *[x ADD]

*[[] SUM] -> 0
*[[[.x] .y] SUM] -> *[[x .y] SUM]
*[[x .y] SUM] -> x + *[y SUM]
*[x SUM] -> *[x SUM]

*[[x .y] FIRST] -> x
*[x FIRST] -> *[x FIRST]

*[[x .y] REST] -> y
*[x REST] -> *[x REST]

*[[x 0] PART] -> x
*[[[x .y] 1] PART] -> x
*[[x [.y]] PART] -> *[[x y] PART]
*[[[x .y] z] PART] -> *[[y z - 1] PART]
*[x PART] -> *[x PART]

*[[x [.y]] START] -> [x .y]
*[x START] -> *[x START]

*[[[.x] y] END] -> [.x y]
*[x END] -> *[x END]

*x -> *x


