Not bad. I've just added a kitchen sink of opcodes at the moment, we can remove them later eg. ADD since it's (kind of) clearly a more complicated and less useful SUM (not like I'm Kelvin versioning these prototypes)


let's expand on this:

[.x] -> x

*[x F] -> x

*[[.x] INC] -> [x INC]
*[x INC] -> x + 1

*[[[.x] y] ADD] -> *[[x y] ADD]
*[[x [.y]] ADD] -> *[[x y] ADD]
*[[x y] ADD] -> x + y
*[x ADD] -> *[x ADD]

*[[] SUM] -> 0
*[[[.x] .y] SUM] -> *[[x .y] SUM]
*[[x .y] SUM] -> x + *[y SUM]
*[x SUM] -> *[x SUM]

*[[x .y] FIRST] -> x
*[x FIRST] -> *[x FIRST]

*[[x .y] REST] -> y
*[x REST] -> *[x REST]

*[[x 0] PART] -> x
*[[[x .y] 1] PART] -> x
*[[x [.y]] PART] -> *[[x y] PART]
*[[[x .y] z] PART] -> *[[y z - 1] PART]
*[x PART] -> *[x PART]

*[[x [.y]] START] -> [x .y]
*[x START] -> *[x START]

*[[[.x] y] END] -> [.x y]
*[x END] -> *[x END]

*[[.x] TYPE] -> 0
*[x TYPE] -> 1

*[[x x] CHECK] -> 0
*[[x y] CHECK] -> 1
*[x CHECK] -> *[x CHECK]

*[[] CHECK2] -> 0
*[[x] CHECK2] -> 0
*[[x x .y] CHECK2] -> *[[x .y] CHECK2]
*[[x y .z] CHECK2] -> 1
*[x CHECK2] -> *[x CHECK2]

*[[] LEN] -> 0
*[[x] LEN] -> 1
*[[x .y] LEN] -> 1 + *[.y LEN]
*[x LEN] -> *[x LEN]

*[x y] -> *[x y]
*[x y .z] -> *[*[x y] .z]
*x -> *x


