	*[[2] LEN]
	1
1 + 1
2


ok now we need something to allow us to write actual programs

[.x] -> x

*[[] SUM] -> 0
*[[[.x] .y] SUM] -> *[[x .y] SUM]
*[[x .y] SUM] -> x + *[y SUM]

*[[x .y] REST] -> y

*[x [PART 0]] -> x
*[[x .y] [PART 1]] -> x
*[x [PART [.y]]] -> *[x [PART y]]
*[[x .y] [PART z]] -> *[y [PART z - 1]]

*[[.x] [START y]] -> [y .x]

*[[.x] [END y]] -> [.x y]

*[[.x] TYPE] -> 0
*[x TYPE] -> 1

*[[] CHECK] -> 0
*[[x] CHECK] -> 0
*[[x x .y] CHECK] -> *[[x .y] CHECK]
*[[x y .z] CHECK] -> 1

*[[] LEN] -> 0
*[[x] LEN] -> 1
*[[x .y] LEN] -> 1 + *[y LEN]

*[[x y z] SPLIT] -> *[*[x y] *[x z]]

*[0 [IF x y]] -> x
*[1 [IF x y]] -> y

*[x y] -> *[x y]
*[x y .z] -> *[*[x y] .z]
*x -> *x


&more evals

*[[x y z] SPLIT]
*[*[x y] *[x z]]

*[[[x y] [PART 1] [PART 2]] SPLIT]
*[*[[x y] [PART 1]] *[[x y] [PART 2]]]
	*[[x y] [PART 1]]
	x
*[x *[[x y] [PART 2]]]
	*[[x y] [PART 2]]
	*[[y] [PART 2 - 1]]
		2 - 1
		1
	*[[y] [PART 1]]
	y
*[x y]
~

*[0 [IF 1 2]]
1

*[1 [IF 1 2]]
2

*[2 [IF 1 2]]
~


ok we need a constant ig

[.x] -> x

*[x [TAKE y]] -> y

*[[] SUM] -> 0
*[[[.x] .y] SUM] -> *[[x .y] SUM]
*[[x .y] SUM] -> x + *[y SUM]

*[[x .y] REST] -> y

*[x [PART 0]] -> x
*[[x .y] [PART 1]] -> x
*[x [PART [.y]]] -> *[x [PART y]]
*[[x .y] [PART z]] -> *[y [PART z - 1]]

*[[.x] [START y]] -> [y .x]

*[[.x] [END y]] -> [.x y]

*[[.x] TYPE] -> 0
*[x TYPE] -> 1

*[[] CHECK] -> 0
*[[x] CHECK] -> 0
*[[x x .y] CHECK] -> *[[x .y] CHECK]
*[[x y .z] CHECK] -> 1

*[[] LEN] -> 0
*[[x] LEN] -> 1
*[[x .y] LEN] -> 1 + *[y LEN]

*[x [SPLIT y z]] -> *[*[x y] *[x z]]

*[w [IF x y z]] -> ?[*[w x] *[w y] *[w z]]
	?[0 x y] -> x
	?[1 x y] -> y

*[x [EXEC y z]] -> *[[*[x y] x] z]

*[x y] -> *[x y]
*[x y .z] -> *[*[x y] .z]
*x -> *x


Again this is starting to look too much like Nock. Honestly I don't think this has much more potential than as displayed here

